replies.bodyText:
Also, the entire class is unnecessary. This can be put in the NodeAdapter as a general-purpose factory method:
    public <T> List<T> asList(String paramName, Function<NodeAdapter, T> factory) {
        List<T> result = new ArrayList<>();
        int i = 0;
        for (JsonNode node : param(paramName)) {
            String pName = paramName + "[" + i + "]";
            NodeAdapter child = new NodeAdapter(node, source, fullPath(pName));
            children.add(child);
            result.add(factory.apply(child));
            ++i;
        }
        return result;
    }

Remember to add unit test as well:
@Test
    public void objectAsList() {
        NodeAdapter subject  = newNodeAdapterForTest("{ key : [{ a: 'I' }, { a: '2' } ] }");

        List<String> result = subject.asList("key", a -> a.asText("a"));

        assertEquals("[I, 2]", result.toString());
    }

